.TH AARU 1 "@DATE@" "Aaru @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aaru \- data preservation suite for optical, magnetic and solid-state media
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aaru
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ options ...]
.PP
.B aaru gui
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Aaru
is a cross-platform data preservation suite. It dumps optical and
removable media (CD, DVD, HD-DVD, Blu-ray, UMD, GameCube/Wii optical,
floppy disks, magneto-optical) to byte-perfect images, decodes their
filesystems, validates checksums, and produces metadata in the CICM
format used by preservation projects.
.PP
The same
.B aaru
binary serves both a command-line interface (default) and an
Avalonia-based graphical interface, the latter launched as
.BR "aaru gui" .
.SH DRIVE ACCESS
.B aaru
ships with the
.B cap_sys_rawio
file capability set, so vendor SCSI passthrough commands work without
sudo.
.PP
The invoking user still needs read/write access to the device node
.RB ( /dev/sr* ,
.BR /dev/sg* ,
removable USB or floppy nodes). On a desktop session at the local seat
this is granted automatically via systemd-logind's
.B uaccess
ACL. For headless use (SSH, cron, systemd
.BR \-\-user ,
NFS-mounted device nodes) add the user to the
.B cdrom
group:
.PP
.RS
.EX
sudo usermod -aG cdrom $USER
newgrp cdrom
.EE
.RE
.SH "COMMAND REFERENCE"
The following is the complete command tree of the
.B aaru
binary shipped in this package, reproduced verbatim from its
.B \-\-help
output. It is regenerated from the binary at package build time, so it
always matches the installed version; run
.B aaru \fICOMMAND\fB \-\-help
for the same text interactively.
.PP
@AARU_COMMAND_REFERENCE@
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/aaru
Wrapper script that delegates to
.IR /usr/lib64/aaru/aaru .
.TP
.I /usr/lib64/aaru/
Real binary, dependent .NET assemblies, native libraries (SkiaSharp,
Avalonia native), and runtime-specific extras.
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/aaru.desktop
Desktop launcher entry (
.B Exec=aaru gui
) that picks up the Avalonia GUI.
.TP
.I ~/.config/Aaru.json
Per-user settings written by
.BR "aaru configure" .
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/Aaru/
Per-user device/media database, statistics and device reports.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/aaru/
Upstream README, Changelog and contributor guide.
.SH NOTES
The command reference above is generated mechanically from the shipped
binary's
.B \-\-help
output during packaging, so it cannot drift from the installed version.
The surrounding sections (drive access, files, see also) are
maintained by hand as part of the Fedora packaging \(em upstream
provides no manpage.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR redumper (1),
.BR discimagecreator (1)
.PP
Upstream documentation, bug tracker and release notes:
.UR https://github.com/aaru-dps/Aaru
.UE .
.SH AUTHOR
Upstream lead: Natalia Portillo
.RB ( https://github.com/claunia ).
.PP
Fedora packaging maintained as part of the COPR repository
.I gmipf/media-preservation .
